definition.value: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by sediment permeated by non-saline water.
An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by sediment permeated by saline water.

label.value: environment determined by a biofilm on a non-saline surface

definition.value: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by a biofilm on a surface which is exposed to non-saline materials.
An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by an aerosol.
An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by a saline aerosol.
An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by an aerosol with a low concentration of dissolved solutes.

label.value: environment associated with an animal part or small animal

definition.value: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead animal, or a whole small animal.

label.value: environment determined by a biofilm on a saline surface

definition.value: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by a biofilm on a surface which is exposed to saline materials.

label.value: environment associated with a plant part or small plant

definition.value: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead plant, or a whole small plant.

label.value: environment associated with a fungal tissue

definition.value: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead fungus.
A cell culture which is composed of a microbial community of known composition.
Mock communities are typically used as positive controls in experiments.
A cell culture which is composed of a single population of bacterial or archaeal cells.

value.value: A lake which is contained within a caldera.
A lake contained within a crater.

definition.value: Note that this class does not commit to what kind of crater contains the lake in question. Please see the subclasses for more specificity.

value.value: Water which has an appreciable concentration of dissolved oxygen.

definition.value: The threshold dissolved oxygen concentration past which water is considered oxic is variable. Typically, this is understood as the concentration at and beyond which organisms inhabiting that water can sustain aerobic metabolism and good health. For most systems, this is above 80% oxygen saturation. Input is welcome here https://github.com/EnvironmentOntology/envo/issues/536

value.value: Water which has low levels of dissolved oxygen.

definition.value: As with oxic and anoxic water, the thresholds for hypoxia are variable. Typically, a hypoxic state is asserted when dissolved oxygen levels decrease to a level where they have detrimental effects on aerobic aquatic organisms, typically below 30% oxygen saturation.

value.value: A lake which is contained in a crater formed by a meteorite impact.
An impact event is a collision between astronomical bodies.
An impact event during which a meteoroid collides with another astronomical body.
An astronomical body which is composed of rocky or metallic materials and is considerably smaller than asteroids.
A material which is composed primarily of one or more pure metals and which shows their properties.

definition.value: While this class allows for some degree of contamination by non-metal substances, the material represented should show at least some of the typical features of a pure metal: hardness (except for liquid metals), opacity, lustre, malleability, fusibility, ductile  and good electrical and thermal conductivity.

value.value: A lake which is contained in a crater formed by an impact event.
A crater which was formed as a result of the impact of one astronomical body on another.

definition.value: A lake which is primarily composed of anoxic water.

value.value: A lake which has a hypolimnion composed primarily of anoxic water.
A lake which has a hypolimnion composed primarily of hypoxic water.

definition.value: A lake which is primarily composed of hypoxic water.
A lake which is primarily composed of oxic water.

value.value: A lake which has a hypolimnion composed primarily of oxic water.
Environmental variability which inheres in an astronomical body part or in outer space.

definition.value: This class refers to all weather, including atmospheric and space weather. Please use a subclass for more specificity.

value.value: Weather which inheres in an atmosphere.

definition.value: This class refers to the common usage of "weather", referencing the state of a (part of) an astronomical body's atmosphere.

value.value: Weather which inheres in outer space.

definition.value: A condition which inheres in an environmental system by virtue of that system undergoing variation in its composition, the distribution of the qualities its components bear, and/or in the processes which occur within it and which it participates in.
This class is very general, but the nature of environmental variability is indeed quite variable. This class may be refined once we have more subclasses to consider.

value.value: The disposition of an environmental system, particularly those influencing atmospheres, to manifest a cyclic pattern of weather over time.

Climate is commonly defined as the weather averaged, or otherwise summarised, over a period of time much longer than the duration of any phenomenon that constitutes weather. The standard averaging period is 30 years, but other periods may be used depending on the purpose.
A process during which water vapour condensing in the atmosphere aggregates into clouds.
A process during which microscopic solid or liquid objects are formed.
An aerosol formation process which occurs in an atmosphere.

label.value: formation of a solid aerosol in an atmosphere

value.value: A process during which an aerosol, consisting of solid particulates suspended in a gas, is formed in an atmosphere.

label.value: formation of a liquid aerosol in an atmosphere

value.value: A process during which an aerosol, consisting of droplets of liquid suspended in gas, is formed in an atmosphere.
An aerosol which has non-gaseous parts that are primarily composed of liquid droplets.
An aerosol which has non-gaseous parts that are primarily composed of solid particles.

label.value: formation of a solid aerosol from gaseous material in an atmosphere

value.value: A process during which microscopic solid particulates are formed from gaseous materials in an atmosphere.

label.value: formation of a liquid aerosol from gaseous material in an atmosphere

value.value: A process during which microscopic liquid droplets are formed from gaseous materials in an atmosphere.
A lake which is contained in a depression formed by the deformation and resulting lateral and vertical movements of a lithosphere.
A process during which pieces of a planetary crust and uppermost mantle move.
A process during which pieces of a planetary crust and uppermost mantle move towards one another.
A process during which pieces of a planetary crust and uppermost mantle move away from one another.

A process during which pieces of a planetary crust and uppermost mantle move along each other in a predominantly horizontal manner, either in a sinistral (left lateral) or dextral (right lateral) direction.
A part of a lithosphere which is separated by other such parts by geographic faults or similar geomorphological discontinuities.
A geomorphological feature which is formed where two or more tectonic plates move towards, away from, or along one another, resulting in deformation of the lithosphere.
